BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:BAg2VaK4hvWGSgQrkqD27
SUMMARY:AI Practitioner Part 1: Introduction to Artificial Intelligence
DTSTAMP:20260412T043251Z
DTSTART:20260413T200000Z
DESCRIPTION:Monday\, April 13\, 2026\, 1 - 4pm\n\nIn this AI foundational 6
	-part series\, you will learn fundamental concepts and terminology related
	 to artificial intelligence\, machine learning\, deep learning\, and gener
	ative AI.\n\nLocation Link:\n\nCentral Library\n\nRoom Location: Level 4 -
	 Room 4\n\nRegistration Required: Registration is not required.\n\nDetaile
	d Description: Explore the relationships between these different AI approa
	ches and understand how to distinguish scenarios suited for traditional so
	ftware methods versus AI/ML techniques.\, This session covers key AWS AI s
	ervices and their capabilities\, including Amazon SageMaker\, Amazon Bedro
	ck\, and pre-trained AI services. You will be introduced to foundation mod
	els\, how they work\, and important considerations when using them\, such 
	as potential risks and strategies for optimizing outputs. By the end of th
	e session\, you will have a broad understanding of AI concepts\, AWS tools
	 for AI development\, and foundational knowledge to continue learning abou
	t generative AI and responsible AI practices.\,\n\nIn this session\, you w
	ill learn to:\n\nDefine artificial intelligence and machine learning termi
	nology\, Explain the relationship between the concepts of AI\, machine lea
	rning\, deep learning\, and generative AI\, Distinguish between scenarios 
	that are suited for traditional software methods\, traditional ML methods\
	, or generative AI\, Identify the capabilities of AWS managed AI/ML servic
	es\, Explain how tokens\, vectors\, and embeddings are used in a generativ
	e AI model\, Describe the effect of model parameters on model outputs\, Di
	scuss the factors to consider when selecting a foundation model\, This ses
	sion is intended for one or more of the following: Individuals who are rea
	dy to learn about AWS AI related technologies\, Individuals in both techni
	cal and non-technical roles\, Individuals looking reskill for the AWS Clou
	d\, Business decision makers\, It is recommended that you have the followi
	ng general skills: Understanding of AWS global infrastructure\, Understand
	ing of AWS networking services and how to build a functioning Amazon VPC s
	olution\, Understanding of Amazon S3\, Amazon EBS\, and Amazon EFS\, Under
	standing of AWS security services\, Understanding of virtual computer serv
	ices using Amazon EC2\, These skills can be gained by taking the following
	 AWS Skills Center session: AWS Skills Centers: Becoming a Cloud Practitio
	ner - Parts 1-4\, Thanks to our partner\n\nAWS Skills Center Seattle .\n\n
	Event Logistics: The program aligns with concepts covered in the AWS Certi
	fied AI Practitioner exam but is designed as an introductory overview rath
	er than exam preparation. The classes are led by AWS Certified Instructors
	 and in partnership with the\n\nAWS Skills Centers .\n\nContact Us: If you
	 have questions about this event\,\n\nAsk Us\n\nor call 206-386-4636.\n\nA
	DA Accommodations: We can provide accommodations for people with disabilit
	ies at Library events. Please\n\ncontactLEAP\n\nat least seven days before
	 the event to request accommodations.\, All Library programs are free and 
	open to the public.\,\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/ai-
	practitioner-part-1-introduction-to-artificial-intelligence/18572328/2026-
	04-13T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/ai-practitioner-part-1-in
	troduction-to-artificial-intelligence/18572328/2026-04-13T00
LOCATION:MAKERS\, 92 Lenora Street\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-arts
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT3H
END:VEVENT
