BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:6Em0boUIeGJbEtvxmggpb
SUMMARY:Low Vision Book Group: "West with Giraffes"
DTSTAMP:20260412T043251Z
DTSTART:20260414T183000Z
DESCRIPTION:Tuesday\, April 14\, 2026\, 11:30am - 1pm\n\nJoin our Low Visio
	n Book Club for a discussion of "West with Giraffes" by Lynda Rutledge.\n\
	nLocation Link:\n\nCentral Library\n\nRoom Location: Level 4 - Room 6\n\nR
	egistration Required: Registration is not required.\n\nDetailed Descriptio
	n:\n\nAbout the book:\, Woodrow Wilson Nickel\, age 105\, feels his life e
	bbing away. But when he learns giraffes are going extinct\, he finds himse
	lf recalling the unforgettable experience he cannot take to his grave. It'
	s 1938. The Great Depression lingers. Hitler is threatening Europe\, and w
	orld-weary Americans long for wonder. They find it in two giraffes who mir
	aculously survive a hurricane while crossing the Atlantic. What follows is
	 a twelve-day road trip in a custom truck to deliver Southern California's
	 first giraffes to the San Diego Zoo. Behind the wheel is the young Dust B
	owl rowdy Woodrow. Inspired by true events\, the tale weaves real-life fig
	ures with fictional ones\, including the world's first female zoo director
	\, a crusty old man with a past\, a young female photographer with a secre
	t\, and assorted reprobates as spotty as the giraffes. Part adventure\, pa
	rt historical saga\, and part coming-of-age love story\, West with Giraffe
	s explores what it means to be changed by the grace of animals\, the kindn
	ess of strangers\, the passing of time\, and a story told before it's too 
	late.\n\nEvent Logistics: View in catalog: "  West With Giraffes " byLynda
	Rutledge.\n\nContact Us: If you have questions about this event\,\n\nAsk U
	s\n\nor call 206-386-4636.\n\nADA Accommodations: We can provide accommoda
	tions for people with disabilities at Library events. Please\n\ncontactLEA
	P\n\nat least seven days before the event to request accommodations.\, All
	 Library programs are free and open to the public.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6am
	city.com/events/#/details/low-vision-book-group-west-with-giraffes/1857233
	1/2026-04-14T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/low-vision-book-group-wes
	t-with-giraffes/18572331/2026-04-14T00
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-arts
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT1H30M
END:VEVENT
